# Skills backup versioning (mandatory)

## Hard rule

**Every time** a skill is created, updated, modified, enhanced, moved, renamed,
or otherwise changed — in `~/.cursor/skills`, any repo `.cursor/skills`, or while
following `create-skill` — you MUST also write a versioned backup under:

`C:\Users\tgaut\OneDrive\Skills Backup`

## How

```bat
node "C:\Users\tgaut\OneDrive\Skills Backup\_tools\backup-skills.js" --only-changed
```

Or for one skill:

```bat
node "C:\Users\tgaut\OneDrive\Skills Backup\_tools\backup-skills.js" --skill <skill-name>
```

## Layout reminder

- `<skill>/base/` = original snapshot (do not overwrite lightly)
- `<skill>/mods/<UTC-timestamp>/` = later full snapshot + `DIFF.patch` vs previous
- `<skill>/LATEST.txt` = path to newest snapshot (may be several layers deep under `mods/`)

Read `C:\Users\tgaut\OneDrive\Skills Backup\README.md` for revert instructions.

## Do not skip

- Applies to **past** skills (initial backup) and **all future** skill changes.
- Applies to personal skills and project-mirrored skills.
- Do not commit secrets into backups; skills should not contain tokens.
